The paper deals with the problem of finding a translation that minimizes the discrete Frechet distance between two sequences of points, which is a fundamental problem in computational geometry (cs.CG). The algorithmic approach involves dynamic programming, which is a common technique in algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The problem of measuring similarity between sequences is also relevant to data mining (cs.DM) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the application of the algorithm to comparing sequences of points in R2 suggests a potential connection to computer vision (cs.CV).
